<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="601" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[708,1301,2827,3246]" pageId="4" pageNumber="601">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1896" box="[709,899,2941,2970]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Acomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="601" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="louisae">Acomys louisae</taxonomicName>
was placed in subgenus Peracomys by F. Petter and J. Roche in 1981 and extracted from the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[996,1190,3015,3049]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Acomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="601" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subspinosus">A. subspinosus</taxonomicName>
species group based on dental characteristics; its validity as a species was later confirmed by broader morphological grounds. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
