<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="601" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[96,1302,3261,3482]" lastBlockId="4.[1365,2573,300,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="601">
Descriptive notes. Head—body 79-95 mm, tail 86-104 mm, ear 12-15 mm, hindfoot 16 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. Louise’s Spiny Mouse is one of the smallest species of 
<taxonomicName box="[417,512,3409,3443]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Acomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="601" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Acomys</taxonomicName>
. Tail is 109% of head-body length. Dorsum is brown or grayish brown, with dull brown spines. Belly is pure white, with soft hairs well demarcated from flanks, which are similar to back. Limbs and feet are also white. Presence of t7 cusp on M' and M* is diagnostic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[1365,2573,300,644]" box="[1366,2438,374,408]" pageId="4" pageNumber="601">Habitat. Somali-Masai bushland from coastal plain to elevations of ¢.1500 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
